led person is liable”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/s762/d/6/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203, § 762(d)(6)(A)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “(as defined in section 206B of the Gramm-Leach-Bliley Act)” after “security-based swap agreement”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/s929O"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203, § 929O","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or recklessly” after “knowingly”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/s762/d/6/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203, § 762(d)(6)(B)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “(as defined in section 206B of the Gramm-Leach-Bliley Act)” after “security-based swap agreements”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/554/s1/a/5/tIII/s303/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–554, § 1(a)(5) [title III, § 303(i)]","children":[],"tail":", amended subsec. (d) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (d) read as follows: “Wherever communicating, or purchasing or selling a security while in possession of, material nonpublic information would violate, or result in liability to any purchaser or seller of the security under any provision of this chapter, or any rule or regulation thereunder, such conduct in connection with a purchase or sale of a put, call, straddle, option,, privilege, or security futures product with respect to such security or with respect to a group or index of securities including such security, shall also violate and result in comparable liability to any purchaser or seller of that security under such provision, rule, or regulation.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/554/s1/a/5/tII/s205/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–554, § 1(a)(5) [title II, § 205(a)(3)]","children":[],"tail":", substituted “, privilege, or security futures product” for “or privilege”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/554/s1/a/5/tIII/s303/j"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–554, § 1(a)(5) [title III, § 303(j)]","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (f)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1998—Subsecs. (e), (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/353"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–353","children":[],"tail":" redesignated subsec. (f) as (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1995—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/67/s104/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–67, § 104(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “liability of controlling persons and persons who aid and abet violations” for “Liabilities of controlling persons” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/67/s104/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–67, § 104(2)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (f)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/376"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–376","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1964—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/467"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–467","children":[],"tail":" extended application of provisions of subsec. (c) by substituting the prohibition against any officer or director of, or an owner of securities issued by, a company from hindering, delaying, or obstructing the preparation or filing of any report, document, or information required to be filed under this chapter for existing provisions applicable only to filings by companies with securities registered on a national securities exchange or subject to the provisions of section 78"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"ta